</paragraph>
<caption id="25536C748399BFA1057315D45A947CDE" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
<paragraph id="8CF10C5B556EDB68692A547D06594EA4" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
Figure 5. Phylogenetic relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="AA353ADA763A9C9D5FD3B6367571D7B9" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hygrophoraceae" genus="Hygrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hygrophorus" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hygrophorus</taxonomicName>
spp. and its ECM roots from Pakistan and their allied 
<taxonomicName id="6CD39E131DD118C9DF65B2D394383C74" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hygrophoraceae" genus="Hygrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hygrophorus" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hygrophorus</taxonomicName>
species based on nrDNA ITS sequences using the Maximum Likelihood method. Sequences generated during this study are in bold letters. Sequences from root tips were labelled as ECM.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="23CA7BA02977F7B68F8CB8B822D4802F" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
<paragraph id="E9E2A28710347BE7D349B5C916140F75" pageId="6" pageNumber="39">
Figure 6. Molecular phylogenetic analysis of 
<taxonomicName id="92095A44901B7069057041A2E18A1133" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hygrophoraceae" genus="Hygrophorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hygrophorus" order="Agaricales" pageId="6" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hygrophorus</taxonomicName>
